text: Wuttke is a German locational surname, which originally meant a person from Wutike, near Neuruppin, Germany.Dictionary of American Family Names. "Wuttke Family History", Oxford University Press, 2013. Retrieved on 7 January 2016. The name may refer to: *Adolf Wuttke (1819–1870), German theologian *Dietmar Wuttke (born 1978), German football player *Friedemann Wuttke, German classical guitarist *Heinrich Wuttke (1818–1876), German historian *Jörg Elling Wuttke (born 1970), German musician *Martin Wuttke (born 1962), German actor *Tim Wuttke (born 1987), German football player *Wolfram Wuttke (1961–2015), German football player ==Fiction== *Peter Wuttke, fictional character in the German television series Die Wochenshow ==References== Category:German-language surnames
title: Wuttke
